There are several barriers to becoming "fluent" in writing code.  

Two of the most important are the memory barrier and the design barrier.

#datascience #programming #rstats #Python

If you want to become "fluent" in data science, then follow me here on Twitter: @Josh_Ebner 

Almost every day, I post tips, strategies, and tutorials to help you master data science FAST.

#DataScience #Python #Rstats https://t.co/o0WMExWZEy

When you overcome the memory barrier, you'll be able to write many short pieces of code quickly, rapidly, and from memory.

#datascience #programming #rstats #Python

So to summarize ... 

If you want to become fluent in writing code, you need to:

‚Äì practice small pieces of syntax
‚Äì use memory hacks to remember syntax
‚Äì practice working on projects
‚Äì get good feedback or mentorship

#datascience #programming #rstats #Python

The memory barrier is simply related to your memory of the syntax.  

Do you sometimes forget syntax and need to look it up?

That's normal, but it's a major barrier to fluency.
